The paper discusses the vulnerability of machine learning models to input data manipulation by adversaries, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves implementing an array of learners and strategically activating them, which is a technique related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves analyzing the Nash equilibrium in a strategic learning environment, which is related to game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.CR, followed by cs.AI, cs.DS, and cs.IT.
